    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and your<strong> harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>harissa stock</strong></p><p>Once the courgette has softened, add the <strong>harissa stock</strong> and your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and cook for 10-12 min or until the sauce has thickened to a bolognese-like consistency and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>harissa pork & beef mince ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
